The paper deals with capacity achieving input covariance matrices of multiantenna channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The main result of the paper is based on the group of symmetries of the matrix of propagation coefficients, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of symmetry and group theory (cs.SY). The paper also uses techniques from matrix manipulation (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) to establish its results. Finally, the paper provides a precise explanation of the dependence of capacity achieving input covariance matrices on the symmetries of the matrix of propagation coefficients, which may fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
